T1  - General equilibrium and international trade with exhaustible resources
AU  - van Geldrop, Jan H.
AU  - Withagen, Cees A.A.M.
JO  - Journal of International Economics
VL  - 34
IS  - 3
SP  - 341
EP  - 357
PY  - 1993
DA  - 1993/05/01/
SN  - 0022-1996
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0022-1996(93)90054-2
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0022199693900542
AB  - The pricing of raw materials from an exhaustible resource is predominantly analysed within the context of a partial equilibrium. It is argued here that there are good reasons for a general equilibrium analysis. In this paper we present an international trade model with exhaustible resources and characterize the general equilibrium properties. The general perspective adopted leads to new insights compared with a partial equilibrium approach.
